ary\n|sugar of Candy\n|sugar of Cipre\n|sugar of flesh\n|sugar of iron\n|sugar of lead\n|sugar of Marrokes\n|sugar of milk\n|sugar of muscle\n|sugar of Saturn\n|sugar of steel\n|sugar on snow,sugar-on-snow\n|sugar orchard,sugar-orchard\n|sugar palm\n|sugar paper,sugar-paper\n|sugar pea\n|sugar-pear\n|sugar pease\n|sugar-pellet\n|sugar-penide\n|sugar-phosphatase\n|sugar-pie\n|sugar pill\n|sugar pine,sugar-pine\n|sugar plantation\n|sugar-plate\n|sugar plum,sugar-plum,sugarplum\n|sugar pucker\n|sugar puff\n|Sugar Puffs\n|sugar-pumpkin\n|sugar push\n|sugar quartz\n|sugar rag\n|sugar-reed\n|sugar-refiner\n|sugar refinery,sugar-refinery\n|sugar-refining\n|sugar residue\n|Sugar River\n|sugar-roll\n|sugar royal\n|sugar-roset\n|sugar rush\n|sugar sack\n|sugar sand\n|sugar-sensitivity\n|sugar shack,sugar shanty\n|sugar shell\n|sugar sickness\n|sugar sifter\n|sugar snap,sugar snap pea\n|sugar snow\n|sugar-snuff\n|sugar soap\n|sugar-sop\n|sugar sorghum\n|sugar-spar\n|sugar-spirit\n|sugar spoon\n|sugar squirrel\n|sugar stick\n|sugar substitute\n|sugar sumac\n|sugar-sweet\n|sugar syrup\n|sugar-teat\n|sugar test\n|sugar thermometer\n|sugartime\n|sugar tit,sugar-tit\n|sugar tongs\n|sugar tree,sugar-tree\n|sugar trough\n|sugar tumor,sugar tumour\n|Sugar Valley\n|sugar vase\n|sugar-vinegar\n|sugar-wash\n|sugar water\n|sugar-weather\n|sugar weed\n|sugar-wood\n|sugar-work\n|sugar-worm\n|sugar-wrack\n|sugary\n|superfine sugar\n|superior sugar\n|sweet as sugar\n|syntactic sugar\n|table sugar\n|threshold sugar\n|triple sugar iron agar\n|true sugar\n|turbinado sugar\n|uncrystallisable sugar,uncrystallizable sugar\n|unrefined sugar\n|urine sugar\n|vanilla sugar\n|white sugar\n|wood sugar,wood-sugar\n|yellow sugar\n|a spoonful of sugar helps the medicine go down|a spoonful of sugar makes the medicine go down|anhydro sugar|banded sugar ant|booger sugar|candi sugar|confectioners sugar|deoxy sugar alcohol|lead sugar|made of sugar|nitro sugar|pretty please with sugar on top|sugar and spice|sugar bag|sugar baker|sugar bear|sugar bomb|sugar coat|sugar coated|sugar cream pie|sugar house|sugar in one's tank|sugar mommy|sugar out|sugar parent|sugar paste|sugar phosphate|sugar pie|sugar pimp|sugar report|sugar scoop|sugar skull|sugar walls|sugar-coated|sugar-mill|sure as sugar\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{col-top|2|desc}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|abe|sogal}}\n* {{desc|rop|juga}}\n* {{desc|rop|suga}}\n* {{desc|bzj|shuga}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|bi|suga}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|cr|ᓲᑳᐤ}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|fj|suka}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|gil|tioka}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|iu|ᓱᑲᒃ}}\n* {{desc|kri|shuga}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|pqm|sukol}} {{q|or from French}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|mi|huka}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|mh|juga}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|sm|suka}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|sn|shuga}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|st|tswekere}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|te|షుగర్|షుగరు}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|tli|shóogaa}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|to|suka}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ts|chukela}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|tn|sukiri}}\n* {{desc|tpi|suga}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|unm|shukël}} {{q|or from Dutch}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|wls|suka}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|zu|ushukela}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{see translation subpage|Noun}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To add sugar to; to [[sweeten]] with sugar.\n#: {{ux|en|John heavily '''sugars''' his coffee.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Teddy and His Friends|author=Emilie Foster|year=1876|passage=See, I've put sugar-plums on his coat for fancy buttons, '''sugared''' his shirt-frill, and put on a red almond to his hat-front.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-1UTMeO9BQEC&dq=%22sugared%20his%22&pg=PA171#v=onepage&q=%22sugared%20his%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|magazine=The Quiver|page=1007|year=1905|passage=\"There spoke the real British scorn,\" she said, '''sugaring''' her tea, \"the fine British contempt for every other nation.\"|title=The Duke of Castle Blanco|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vapMAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22sugaring%20her%22&pg=PA1007#v=onepage&q=%22sugaring%20her%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Hidden Minds: A History of the Unconscious|author=Frank Tallis|year=2002|passage=Moreover, the residents recalled that the aristocrat's pet canary had become like a personal retainer, waking his master in the morning and '''sugaring''' his drink.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aZqbfUpWTsMC&lpg=PA16&dq=%22sugaring%20his%22&pg=PA16#v=onepage&q=%22sugaring%20his%22&f=false}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make (something unpleasant) seem less so.\n#: {{ux|en|She has a gift for '''sugaring''' what would otherwise be harsh words.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Michigan in her pioneer politics|author=Anson De Puy Van Buren|year=1890|passage=He also published the \"Weekly Recorder,\" an indefinite title, which was his way of '''sugaring''' what soon became in the region where it was published, Mt. Pleasant, Ohio, a very bitter pill.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Give My Love to Maria|author=Mrs. Florence Guertin Tuttle|year=1917|passage=She shook her head sadly at him. \"No, it won't do, Arthur. I'm not in a mood to be '''sugared'''.\"|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ePUcAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22sugared%20what%22&pg=PA134#v=onepage&q=%22sugared%20what%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=René Lévesque and the Parti Québécois in Power|author=Graham Fraser|year=2001|passage=But step by step, aided by Claude Morin's arguments, Lévesque had led the party through the process of '''sugaring''' what he saw as the pill of independence.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5Tx01YC8VMcC&lpg=PA170&dq=%22sugaring%20what%22&pg=PA171#v=onepage&q=%22sugaring%20what%22&f=false}}\n# {{lb|en|US|Canada|regional}} In making [[maple sugar]], to complete the process of [[boil]]ing down the [[syrup]] till it is thick enough to [[crystallize]]; to approach or reach the state of [[granulation]]; with the preposition ''off''.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=The Ohio Cultivator|year=1851|volume=7|page=91|passage=To '''sugar''' off, I prefer using a kettle that will hold about half a. barrel; and boil over a brisk, steady fire, till on dropping some of the syrup into cold water it will break like glass, then dip it into wooden trays to cool, and when it is grained stir it briskly.|title=On Making Maple Syrup|author=J. D. H.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|journal=Nindinawemaagan Giwitaa'ayeyii|volume=6|page=55|year=1994|passage=A long time ago my grandmother and I used to boil maple sap. When she '''sugared''' off, I stood there.|title=Sugaring Off}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Canada: A Primary Source Cultural Guide|author=Lois Sakany|year=2004|passage=During the spring in Quebec and Ontario, maple syrup is harvested, or \"'''sugared''' off,\" a process which is usually celebrated as a social event.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JyqGQTuikUYC&lpg=PT97&dq=%22sugared%20off%22%20%22maple%20syrup%22&pg=PT97#v=onepage&q=%22sugared%20off%22%20%22maple%20syrup%22&f=false}}\n# {{lb|en|entomology}} To apply sugar to trees or plants in order to catch [[moth]]s.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|magazine=The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine|year=1876|page=207|volume=12|title=Note on sugaring|author=W. Sandison|passage=Some entomologists assert that it is useless to '''sugar''' when ivy is in bloom.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KJsv9O0kw6QC&dq=%22sugaring%22%20%22moths%22&pg=PA207#v=onepage&q=%22sugaring%22%20%22moths%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Grain and Chaff from an English Manor|author=Arthur Herbert Savory|year=1921|passage=The latter are best taken by \"'''sugaring'''\" — painting patches of mixed beer and sugar on a series of tree trunks, and making several rounds at twilight with a lantern and a cyanide bottle.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PggNAAAAYAAJ&dq=%22sugaring%22%20%22moths%22&pg=PA272#v=onepage&q=%22sugaring%22%20%22moths%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Ecological Census Techniques: A Handbook|author=William J. Sutherland|year=2006|passage='''Sugaring''' attracts some species of moth that do not readily come to light.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rTJdia64ACMC&lpg=PA236&dq=%22sugaring%22%20%22moths%22&pg=PA236#v=onepage&q=%22sugaring%22%20%22moths%22&f=false}}\n# {{lb|en|programming|transitive}} To [[rewrite]] ([[source code]]) using [[syntactic sugar]].\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|year=2002|author=Jonathan Bromley|title=Fixed point arithmetic|newsgroup=comp.arch.fpga\n|passage=You can '''sugar''' the syntax of constants thus: {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-newsgroup|en|year=2006|author=Neil Madden|title=Re: Closures|newsgroup=comp.lang.tcl\n|passage=Sure, you could '''sugar''' the latter to look like the former (effectively implementing closures as objects), but it seems simpler to just allow the former.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[compliment]] (a person).\n# To [[remove]] [[hair]] using a paste of sugar, [[water]]{{,}} and [[lemon juice]].\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|add sugar to}} [[sweeten]]\n* {{sense|make less unpleasant}} [[sweeten]], [[sugar-coat]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col3|en\n|oversugar\n|sugared\n|sugarer\n|sugaring\n|sugar off\n|sugar the pill\n}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top-see|to add sugar to, to sweeten|sweeten}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|suiker}}\n* Arabic:\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|حَلَّى|tr=ḥalla}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|շաքարել}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|ensucrar}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|加甜|tr=jiātián}}, {{t|cmn|加糖|tr=jiātáng}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|søde}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|sukeri}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|sokeroida}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|sucrer}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|adozar}}, {{t+|gl|azucrar}}\n* Georgian: {{t-needed|ka}}\n* German: {{t+|de|zuckern}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|cukroz}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|zuccherare}}\n* Nyelâyu: {{t|yly|chuxee}}\n* Persian: {{t|fa|شیرین کردن|tr=širin kardan}}\n* Piedmontese: {{t|pms|sucré}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|słodzić|impf}}, {{t+|pl|posłodzić|pf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|açucarar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|îndulci}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|са́харить|impf}}, {{t+|ru|поса́харить|pf}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|sladkati}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|azucarar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|sockra}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|şekerlemek}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-see|to make something seem less unpleasant|sugarcoat}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|indsukre}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|pehmentää}}, {{t+|fi|kaunistella}}\n* German: {{t+|de|versüßen}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|zuccherare}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|osładzać|impf}}, {{t|pl|osłodzić|pf}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|açucarar}}, {{t+|pt|suavizar}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|îndulci}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|подсласти́ть|pf}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|sladkati}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|azucarar}}, {{t+|es|endulzar}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|sockra}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{minced oath of|en|shit}}.\n#: {{ux|en|Oh, '''sugar!'''}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Tobias O' the Light: A Story of Cape Cod|author=James A. Cooper|year=1920|passage=\"Oh, '''sugar'''! I suppose that's so,\" reflected Tobias, filling his pipe.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9hMmAAAAMAAJ&dq=%22oh%20sugar%22&pg=PA100#v=onepage&q=%22oh%20sugar%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=If They Only Listened to Us: What Women Voters Want Politicians to Hear|author=Melinda Henneberger|year=2007|passage=But they do not even hope for such a thing in '08, and fear far worse: Sister Suzanne Thibault, a lifelong Republican so mild she shouts, “Oh, '''sugar'''!” when annoyed, posits that if Hillary Clinton were nominated, “She'd get killed, literally assassinated. We have too many right-wing people out there who would do that.\"|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=J3B7EaGvIVYC&lpg=PA153&dq=%22oh%20sugar%22&pg=PA153#v=onepage&q=%22oh%20sugar%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Sultry with a Twist|author=Macy Beckett|year=2012|passage=“Oh, '''sugar'''.” His room was empty.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F0HQBAAAQBAJ&lpg=PT99&dq=%22oh%20sugar%22&pg=PT99#v=onepage&q=%22oh%20sugar%22&f=false}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|en|sugar honey ice tea}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|minced oath}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|vitsi}}, {{t+|fi|pannahinen}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|zut}}, {{t+|fr|fichtre}}, {{t+|fr|mince}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Scheibenkleister|m}}, {{t|de|Scheibenhonig|m}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|siúcra}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|mkrda}}, {{t|pt|ferca}}, {{t|pt|herfa}}, {{t+|pt|merca}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|блин|m|lit=pancake}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|jolines}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* [[glyco-]]\n* [[-ose]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n* {{R:Britannica 1911|Sugar}}\n* {{R:AHD}}\n* {{R:Collins}}\n* {{R:Dictionary.com}}\n* {{R:Etymonline}}\n* {{R:Longman}}\n* {{R:MWO}}\n* {{R:Webster 1913}}\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=agrsu|Argus|Guras|argus|gaurs|guars|ragus|ragùs}}\n\n{{cln|en|endearing terms|minced oaths|terms of address}}\n{{C|en|Sugars}}\n[[Category:Southern US English]]\n\n==Basque==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{compound|eu|su|gar}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|eu|LL-Q8752 (eus)-Xabier Cañas-sugar.wav}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{eu-noun|in}}\n\n# [[flame]]\n\n==Galician==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|gl|chuchar|suchar|zugar}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|gl|la-vul|*sucāre}}, from {{inh|gl|la|sugō|sugere}}, from {{der|gl|ine-pro|*sug-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*suk-}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|gl|[suˈɣaɾ]}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{gl-verb}}\n\n# to [[suck]]\n#* {{quote-book|gl|year=1858|author=O Seor Pedro|title=Romance Gallego...|location=Santiago|publisher=Imprenta de Manuel Mirás|page=2\n|passage=''Deixáradesme ir pra terra, pra que as miñocas as tripas e os ósos me esfuracasen e me '''sugasen''' axiña''\n|translation=''You'll let me go to the earth, so that promptly the earthworms drill and '''suck''' my guts and bones''}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{gl-conj}}\n{{gl-reinteg-conj}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|gl|sugota}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|gl|samesuga}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:roa-opt:CX|semesuga}}\n* {{R:gl:DDLG}}\n* {{R:gl:TILG}}\n* {{R:gl:Estraviz}}\n* {{R:TLPGP|zugar}}\n\n==Ido==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|io|de|saugen}} and {{bor|io|la|sūgō|sūgere}}, and to some extent {{bor|io|en|suck}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|io|/suˈɡar/}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{io-verb|sug}}\n\n# {{lb|io|transitive}} to [[suck]] {{gloss|candy, etc., something from something}}\n#: {{ux|io|'''Sugar''' la suko de oranjo.|'''To suck''' the juice from an orange.}}\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{io-conj}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|io|suganta||sucking; {{qualifier|zool.}} suctorial}}\n* {{l|io|sugilo||sucker {{gloss|as of an insect}}}}\n* {{l|io|mamsugar||to suckle}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{la-IPA|sūgar}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form|head=sūgar}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|sūgō||1|s|futr|pasv|indc}}\n\n==Portuguese==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|pt|la-vul|*sucō|*sucāre}}, from {{inh|pt|la|sugō|sūgere}}, from {{der|pt|ine-pro|*sug-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*suk-}}. Cognate with {{cog|gl|sugar}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n{{pt-IPA}}\n* {{audio|pt|LL-Q5146 (por)-MedK1-sugar.wav|a=<<Brazil>> (<<Caipira>>)}}\n* {{hyph|pt|su|gar}}\n* {{hmp|pt|sogar}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{pt-verb}}\n\n# to [[suck]]\n#: {{syn|pt|chupar|libar}}\n#: {{hypo|pt|mamar}}\n\n=====Conjugation=====\n{{pt-conj}} \n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|pt\n|sugador\n|sugação\n}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|pt\n|sucção\n|suctório\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{wp|pt:relacionamento sugar}}\n{{pseudo-loan|pt|en|sugar<t:money>}} via {{m|en|sugar daddy}}.\n\n====Pronunciation====\n{{rfp|pt|Needs European Portuguese}}\n{{pt-IPA|br=shúgậrh}}\n* {{hyph|pt|su|gar}}\n\n====Adjective====\n{{pt-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|pt|slang}} relating to [[sugar dating]]; of a [[relationship]], involving a partner who spends money on a often younger partner\n#: {{co|pt|relacionamento '''''sugar'''''|'''sugar''' dating}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|pt\n|sugar baby\n|sugar daddy\n|sugar mommy\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:pt:Aulete}}\n* {{R:pt:Infopédia}}\n* {{R:pt:Michaelis}}\n* {{R:pt:Priberam}}\n\n{{cln|pt|unadapted borrowings from English}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{suffix|ro|suge|t1=to suck|-ar}}. Compare {{cog|dlm|sugol||lamb}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|/suˈɡar/}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{ro-adj}}\n\n# [[suckling]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-decl-adj}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|m|sugari|f=sugară}}\n\n# unweaned [[baby]], [[newborn]]\n# [[suckling]], young mammal that hasn't weaned yet\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-m}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|ro|sugaci}}\n\n==Venetan==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|vec|la|exsūcō|exsūcāre|t=to juice; to dry}} (compare {{cog|it|asciugare}}, {{cog|fur|suiâ}}).\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|vec|verb}}\n\n# {{lb|vec|transitive}} to [[wipe]], [[dry]]\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{vec-conj-auto}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|vec|sugaman}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|vec|suto}}"}}